> inline latex with live preview in org-mode<p>This certainly isn&#x27;t the default. Could you elaborate more on how you set this up?<p>Edit: Found my answer. M-x org-preview-latex-fragment, which is bound to C-c C-x C-l.<p>Edit 2: Hey look, you can get tikz working! Evaluate or add this to your .emacs:<p><pre><code>    (add-to-list &#x27;org-latex-packages-alist &#x27;(&quot;&quot; &quot;tikz&quot; t))
    (setq org-latex-create-formula-image-program &#x27;imagemagick)
</code></pre>
Then, type the following into an Org-mode document and press C-c C-x C-l:<p><pre><code>    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.1]
    \draw[fill=green] (3,0) circle (9);
    \draw[fill=orange] (1,0) circle (5);
    \draw[fill=blue] (0,0) circle (3);</code></pre>
\end{tikzpicture}
